**Smart Enumerations in DDD C# Application**

Smart enumerations are a way to make your enumerations more expressive and easier to use. They provide additional information and behavior beyond just the enumeration value.

Here's an example of how you can implement smart enumerations in a DDD C# application:

```csharp
public enum Color
{
    Red,
    Green,
    Blue
}

public class ColorEnum : IColor
{
    public static readonly ColorEnum Red = new ColorEnum(Color.Red);
    public static readonly ColorEnum Green = new ColorEnum(Color.Green);
    public static readonly ColorEnum Blue = new ColorEnum(Color.Blue);

    public Color Value { get; }

    private ColorEnum(Color value)
    {
        Value = value;
    }

    public static implicit operator Color(ColorEnum colorEnum) => colorEnum.Value;
    public static implicit operator ColorEnum(Color color) => FromColor(color);

    public static ColorEnum FromColor(Color color)
    {
        return color switch
        {
            Color.Red => Red,
            Color.Green => Green,
            Color.Blue => Blue,
            _ => throw new ArgumentException("Invalid color", nameof(color))
        };
    }

    public override string ToString() => Value.ToString();
}
```

